# Agent workflow (OttoLog)

Nate has **Cursor Pro+** (no on-demand spend) and wants **high quality with efficient tokens** — not defaulting to one model forever, not burning tokens for sport.

**Scoped chats:** open [`.cursor/skills/scoped-execution-chats/SKILL.md`](../skills/scoped-execution-chats/SKILL.md) when starting a slice, drafting a kickoff, or when a chat is getting long.

## Orchestrator vs execution

| Chat role | Use for | Default model | Commit gate |
|-----------|---------|---------------|-------------|
| **Orchestrator** | Direction, reviews, kickoffs, Status hygiene, “what next?” | **Auto** | Never commit unless Nate says “commit” in that chat |
| **Execution** | Implement a scoped slice / spike / docs pass | **Recommend** a model *below* the kickoff (see below) | Same git gate unless Nate grants commit in the kickoff |

**Balance**
- Keep the orchestrator chat long-lived and relatively thin: decide → kickoff → review summary → Status. Don’t implement large slices in the orchestrator.
- Spin **new** execution chats for each slice/spike. Paste a scoped kickoff (git gate, read list, in/out of scope, Murph acceptance, stop for review).
- Bring results back to the orchestrator; don’t fork product direction in five parallel chats without a merge point.
- Prefer one execution agent finishing a slice over overlapping agents on the same files.

## Model recommendations (do this regularly)

Agents (especially the orchestrator when drafting kickoffs) should **briefly recommend a model** for the next task — 1–2 lines, why, and a cheaper alternative if quality allows. Put that recommendation **underneath** the pasteable kickoff prompt (for Nate), **not inside** the prompt the execution agent will see.

**Defaults**
- **Auto** — orchestrator; light Q&A; Status/docs nits; when unsure.
- **Sonnet 5** — strong mid-range pick for scoped builds (quality + cost). Launch promo through **Aug 31, 2026** (~33% cheaper API rates). Prefer when the task fits; not a ban on larger models.
- Use **Opus 4.8** (or another larger allowlist model) when judgment, ambiguity, or reverse-cost justifies it — don’t default every chat there, and don’t avoid it when it’s the right tool.

### Allowed models only (Nate’s Cursor account)

Recommend **only** from this list (exact display names). Do not suggest models outside it.

| Name | Role |
|------|------|
| **Auto** | Default — orchestrator and when unsure |
| **Composer 2.5** | Fast / mechanical / narrow well-specified slices |
| **Sonnet 5** | Scoped feature builds, mid complexity |
| **Opus 4.8** | Hard product/UX judgment, ambiguous bugs, architecture |
| **Fable 5** | Strong Claude-family alternate when Opus is overkill or for a second Claude pass |
| **GPT-5.6 Sol** | GPT-family build / second opinion |
| **GPT-5.6 Terra** | GPT-family alternate (different GPT pick than Sol) |
| **Cursor Grok 4.5** | Non-Claude/GPT alternate opinion once — then converge |

**Rough fit**

| Task shape | Prefer | Skip / overkill |
|------------|--------|-----------------|
| Orchestration, kickoffs, Status | **Auto** | Opus 4.8 for routine routing |
| Hard product/UX judgment, ambiguous bugs, architecture | **Opus 4.8** | Composer 2.5 alone |
| Scoped feature build (QB Insight chrome, lock polish, screen work) | **Sonnet 5**; **Composer 2.5** if narrow + well-specified | Opus 4.8 unless stuck or high-risk |
| Author feel rethink / open UX forks before code | **Plan** mode + Sonnet 5 or Opus 4.8 | Jumping straight to Agent chrome rewrites |
| Fast mechanical edits, renames, small follow-ups | **Composer 2.5** | Opus 4.8 |
| Alternate opinion / second pass on a stuck design | **GPT-5.6 Sol**, **GPT-5.6 Terra**, **Cursor Grok 4.5**, or **Fable 5** (once) — then converge | Running three models on the same trivial edit |

**Quality bar**
- Max quality when the decision or bug is expensive to reverse (schema, Insights contract, nest chrome DNA).
- Token-aware: tight kickoffs, open only needed docs/images, no wholesale doc pastes, no exploratory rewrites of working code.
- If Auto is doing fine on a task type, say so — don’t upsell.

**When speaking to Nate:** use the exact names above (e.g. “Auto”, “Opus 4.8”, “Sonnet 5”). Don’t dump internal kebab slugs unless he asks.

## Kickoffs should include

**Inside the pasteable prompt** (what the execution agent gets):

1. Git gate (no commit unless asked — unless Nate granted it in the prompt).
2. Read list + gold `.jpg` paths when UI.
3. In / out of scope.
4. Acceptance (Murph / device).
5. Stop for Nate review.

**Outside / below the prompt** (orchestrator → Nate only):

- **Suggested model** (+ optional cheaper fallback) from the allowlist only. Nate picks the model in the new chat; do not bake the recommendation into the agent prompt.
- **Mode** — default **Agent**. Recommend **Plan** when the slice still has open product/UX forks, multi-approach tradeoffs, or Nate should approve the approach before code. Do not put mode inside the agent prompt.
